    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nSince neovim 0.12, shift + arrow keys no longer works in rxvt-unicode\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. nvim --clean\n2. insert some text\n3. use shift-left/right to move between words\n4. nothing happens\n\n### Expected behavior\n\ncursor jumps between words like it did in previous versions (worked fine in neovim 0.11.6)\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 9.2.218\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nDebian testing\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nrxvt-unicode (urxvt) v9.31\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nrxvt-unicode-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nGitHub release",
    "closed_at": "2026-03-31T22:07:12Z",
